definition: band/belt/girdle/ribbon/tire/area/zone/region/CL:條|条[tiao2]/to wear/to carry/to take along/to bear (i.e. to have)/to lead/to bring/to look after/to raise
to come/to arrive/to come round/ever since/next

pinyin: ji1 hui4 dai4 lai2 cheng2 gong1

sentences.english: Ageing will put pressure on societies at all levels.
sentences.chinese: 老龄问题将对社会各阶层带来压力。

sentences.english: The acids in tomato juice can degrade the drink’s other ingredients.
sentences.chinese: 番茄汁中的酸会削弱其他材料带来的味觉。

sentences.english: Hideyoshi himself brought along two portable teahouses in starkly contrasting styles.
sentences.chinese: 丰臣秀吉本人带来了两个风格截然不同的便携式茶馆。

sentences.english: That was Hedwig. She brought a letter from Lupin .
sentences.chinese: 是海德薇，她带来了一封卢平的信。

sentences.english: Quality and moderation often bring more joy than an excess.
sentences.chinese: 品质和适度通常会比超额带来更多的欢乐。

sentences.english: EA brings MONOPOLY's new card game to mobile.
sentences.chinese: 电子艺界垄断带来的新游戏移动。

sentences.english: They are round and so they bring us good luck all the year round.
sentences.chinese: 它们都是圆的，能给我们带来一年的好运气。

sentences.english: Hooley 's Irish Pub brings an authentic slice of Irish culture to Guangzhou.
sentences.chinese: 胡利的爱尔兰酒吧给广州带来了真正的爱尔兰文化片。

sentences.english: I say that because it gives tremendous liquidity to the markets.
sentences.chinese: 我这样说是因为它给市场带来的巨大的流动性。

sentences.english: Rewards for past good deeds will be yours.
sentences.chinese: 往时的善事会给带来报答。

sentences.english: Trouble develops, however, when any human instinct or appetite causes overdeveloped.
sentences.chinese: 但假使人的欲求或喜好过度膨胀则会带来麻烦。

sentences.english: Chinese government is popular with the people because the government brings stability and wealth to the people.
sentences.chinese: 中国政府却因为为人民带来了稳定和财富而深得民心。

sentences.english: Bottom line, you bring in revenue for them, you win, they win.
sentences.chinese: 底线就是，你为他们带来收入，大家双赢。

sentences.english: Music brings my heart fairy air.
Shi Xing pain Chen interests, points out the consequences of the Japanese occupation of Korea will bring.
sentences.chinese: 石星痛陈利害，指出了日军占领朝鲜会带来的恶果。

sentences.english: Papa would bring an old battered coal shovel and an old-fashioned ice chest with him.
sentences.chinese: 爷爷总会带来一把破旧的煤铲和一台老式冰柜。

definition: to give to/to provide to/to bring to/to take to
to/for/for the benefit of/to give/to allow/to do sth (for sb)/(grammatical equivalent of 被)/(grammatical equivalent of 把)/(sentence intensifier)
to arise/to come into being/to come about/to give rise to/to bring into being/to bring about/to produce/to engender/to generate/to appear/appearance/emergence/generation/production/yield
of/~'s (possessive particle)/(used after an attribute)/(used to form a nominal expression)/(used at the end of a declarative sentence for emphasis)
to yield/to permit/to let sb do sth/to have sb do sth/to make sb (feel sad etc)/by (indicates the agent in a passive clause, like 被[bei4])
to create/to bring about/to produce/to set (a record)
auxiliary verb introducing future action: may (be able to)/will (cause)/should (enable)/going to
